Name: atrial heart septal defect 1
Definition: An atrial heart septal defect type 1 associated with variation in the region 5p.

Name: atrial heart septal defect 2
Definition: An atrial heart septal defect type 2 that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the GATA4 gene on chromosome 8p23.

Name: atrial heart septal defect 3
Definition: An atrial heart septal defect type 3 that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the myosin heavy chain-6 gene (MYH6) on chromosome 14q12.

Name: atrial heart septal defect 4
Definition: An atrial heart septal defect type 4 that has_material_basis_in mutation in the TBX20 gene.

Name: atrial heart septal defect 5
Definition: An atrial heart septal defect type 5 that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the ACTC1 gene on chromosome 15q14.

Name: atrial heart septal defect 6
Definition: An atrial heart septal defect type 6 that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the TLL1 gene on chromosome 4q32.

Name: atrial heart septal defect 7
Definition: An atrial heart septal defect that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the NKX2-5 gene on chromosome 5q35.
Synonym: atrial septal defect-atrioventricular conduction defects syndrome

Name: atrial heart septal defect 8
Definition: An atrial heart septal defect that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the CITED2 gene on chromosome 6q23.3.

Name: atrial heart septal defect 9
Definition: An atrial heart septal defect that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the GATA6 gene on chromosome 18q11.

Name: patent foramen ovale
Definition: A sarcoma and malignant tumor of nasal sinuses that is located_in the paranasal sinus.

Name: Lutembacher's syndrome
Definition: A rectum cancer that derives_from epithelial cells of glandular origin.
